## 1. Development Workflow Steps
Follow these steps for new features.

@workflow_rules [
  {
    "id": "create_branch",
    "rule": "Create a feature branch from main.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "git checkout -b feature/my-new-feature"
  },
  {
    "id": "tdd",
    "rule": "Use Test-Driven Development: Write test, implement code, refactor.",
    "severity": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "code_quality",
    "rule": "Run formatters, analyzers, and tests before committing.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "clang-format -i src/**/*.cpp include/**/*.h\nclang-tidy src/**/*.cpp\ncd build && ctest --output-on-failure"
  },
  {
    "id": "create_pr",
    "rule": "Create PR to https://github.com/TiGRoNdev/HyperEngine using MCP tools.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "Ensure tests pass, update docs, describe changes."
  }
]

- Use mcp_github_create_branch for branching.
- Link PRs to issues with mcp_github_create_pull_request.

## 2. Tables for Quick Reference

### Workflow Steps Summary
| Step | Description | Tools/Command |
|------|-------------|---------------|
| 1 | Create branch | git checkout -b |
| 2 | TDD cycle | Write test, code, refactor |
| 3 | Quality check | clang-format, clang-tidy, ctest |
| 4 | Create PR | mcp_github_create_pull_request |

## 3. Best Practices and Enforcement
- Atomic commits with semantic messages.
- Require PR approvals.
- Integrate with GitHub Actions.